### Relationships

| Relation | Type | Target | Notes |
|---|---|---|---|
| `menu_page` | Many-to-One | `menu_page.id` | |
| `product` | Many-to-One | `product.id` | Nullable. Only for `product_card` |

### Notes
- **Live link rule:** for `type = product_card`, `name`, `sale_price`, `description`, and `image` are **never duplicated** into `menu_element` — they are read from `product` on every render of the public menu. If `product.status = inactive` or `product.sellable = false`, the card is **omitted** from the public render (not shown as empty/broken).
- If a linked `product` is hard-deleted (should not normally happen — products are soft-deleted per `_entity-conventions.md`), the `menu_element.product_id` FK uses `ON DELETE SET NULL` and the element is treated as an empty `product_card` (hidden in public view, shown as "producto eliminado, vuelve a vincularlo" in the editor).
- `field_config` only overrides **display**, never price/name values themselves — those always come live from `product`.
- Hard delete: elements are deleted directly (no soft delete), same rationale as `menu_page`.